Bytes from the digital world Show us the cash, McKinsey. The company has yet to pay back the R1bn it got from Eskom, and says it is not responsible for the R560m paid to Trillian. Lurking danger: Facebook and Google. But the problem goes beyond SA. Rob Rose says the South African Revenue Services can’t be bothered to answer ‘mundane questions’ around Jonas Makwakwa’s return. Lobby group the Council for the Advancement of the South African Constitution wants Mxolisi Nxasana returned as the national director of public prosecutions. The Net1 trio keep their board seats — for now. This week’s AGM also reflected shareholders’ frustrations around the scandal over Cash Paymaster Services’ contract with the South African Social Security Agency. Little cheer as Oceana reports "difficult catching environment".